casadi::AmplInterface Class Reference

'AmplInterface' plugin for Nlpsol More...

#include <ampl_interface.hpp>

Detailed Description


List of available options
IdTypeDescription
solverOT_STRINGAMPL solver binary


List of available options
IdTypeDescriptionUsed in
ad_weightOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for derivative calculation.When there is an option of either using forward or reverse mode directional derivatives, the condition ad_weight*nf<=(1-ad_weight)*na is used where nf and na are estimates of the number of forward/reverse mode directional derivatives needed. By default, ad_weight is calculated automatically, but this can be overridden by setting this option. In particular, 0 means forcing forward mode and 1 forcing reverse mode. Leave unset for (class specific) heuristics.casadi::FunctionInternal
ad_weight_spOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for sparsity pattern calculation calculation.Overrides default behavior. Set to 0 and 1 to force forward and reverse mode respectively. Cf. option "ad_weight". When set to -1, sparsity is completely ignored and dense matrices are used.casadi::FunctionInternal
always_inlineOT_BOOLForce inlining.casadi::FunctionInternal
bound_consistencyOT_BOOLEnsure that primal-dual solution is consistent with the boundscasadi::Nlpsol
cacheOT_DICTPrepopulate the function cache. Default: emptycasadi::FunctionInternal
calc_fOT_BOOLCalculate 'f' in the Nlpsol base classcasadi::Nlpsol
calc_gOT_BOOLCalculate 'g' in the Nlpsol base classcasadi::Nlpsol
calc_lam_pOT_BOOLCalculate 'lam_p' in the Nlpsol base classcasadi::Nlpsol
calc_lam_xOT_BOOLCalculate 'lam_x' in the Nlpsol base classcasadi::Nlpsol
calc_multipliersOT_BOOLCalculate Lagrange multipliers in the Nlpsol base classcasadi::Nlpsol
common_optionsOT_DICTOptions for auto-generated functionscasadi::OracleFunction
compilerOT_STRINGJust-in-time compiler plugin to be used.casadi::FunctionInternal
custom_jacobianOT_FUNCTIONOverride CasADi's AD. Use together with 'jac_penalty': 0. Note: Highly experimental. Syntax may break often.casadi::FunctionInternal
der_optionsOT_DICTDefault options to be used to populate forward_options, reverse_options, and jacobian_options before those options are merged in.casadi::FunctionInternal
derivative_ofOT_FUNCTIONThe function is a derivative of another function. The type of derivative (directional derivative, Jacobian) is inferred from the function name.casadi::FunctionInternal
detect_simple_boundsOT_BOOLAutomatically detect simple bounds (lbx/ubx) (default false). This is hopefully beneficial to speed and robustness but may also have adverse affects: 1) Subtleties in heuristics and stopping criteria may change the solution, 2) IPOPT may lie about multipliers of simple equality bounds unless 'fixed_variable_treatment' is set to 'relax_bounds'.casadi::Nlpsol
detect_simple_bounds_is_simpleOT_BOOLVECTORFor internal use only.casadi::Nlpsol
detect_simple_bounds_partsOT_FUNCTIONFor internal use only.casadi::Nlpsol
detect_simple_bounds_target_xOT_INTVECTORFor internal use only.casadi::Nlpsol
discreteOT_BOOLVECTORIndicates which of the variables are discrete, i.e. integer-valuedcasadi::Nlpsol
dumpOT_BOOLDump function to file upon first evaluation. [false]casadi::FunctionInternal
dump_dirOT_STRINGDirectory to dump inputs/outputs to. Make sure the directory exists [.]casadi::FunctionInternal
dump_formatOT_STRINGChoose file format to dump matrices. See DM.from_file [mtx]casadi::FunctionInternal
dump_inOT_BOOLDump numerical values of inputs to file (readable with DM.from_file) [default: false]casadi::FunctionInternal
dump_outOT_BOOLDump numerical values of outputs to file (readable with DM.from_file) [default: false]casadi::FunctionInternal
enable_fdOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation by finite differencing. [default: false]]casadi::FunctionInternal
enable_forwardOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation using generated functions for Jacobian-times-vector products - typically using forward mode AD - if available. [default: true]casadi::FunctionInternal
enable_jacobianOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation using generated functions for Jacobians of all differentiable outputs with respect to all differentiable inputs - if available. [default: true]casadi::FunctionInternal
enable_reverseOT_BOOLEnable derivative calculation using generated functions for transposed Jacobian-times-vector products - typically using reverse mode AD - if available. [default: true]casadi::FunctionInternal
error_on_failOT_BOOLThrow exceptions when function evaluation fails (default true).casadi::ProtoFunction
eval_errors_fatalOT_BOOLWhen errors occur during evaluation of f,g,...,stop the iterationscasadi::Nlpsol

ignore_check_vecOT_BOOLIf set to true, the input shape of F will not be checked.casadi::Nlpsol
input_schemeOT_STRINGVECTORDeprecated option (ignored)casadi::FunctionInternal
inputs_checkOT_BOOLThrow exceptions when the numerical values of the inputs don't make sensecasadi::FunctionInternal
is_diff_inOT_BOOLVECTORIndicate for each input if it should be differentiable.casadi::FunctionInternal
is_diff_outOT_BOOLVECTORIndicate for each output if it should be differentiable.casadi::FunctionInternal
iteration_callbackOT_FUNCTIONA function that will be called at each iteration with the solver as input. Check documentation of Callback.casadi::Nlpsol
iteration_callback_ignore_errorsOT_BOOLIf set to true, errors thrown by iteration_callback will be ignored.casadi::Nlpsol
iteration_callback_stepOT_INTOnly call the callback function every few iterations.casadi::Nlpsol
jac_penaltyOT_DOUBLEWhen requested for a number of forward/reverse directions, it may be cheaper to compute first the full jacobian and then multiply with seeds, rather than obtain the requested directions in a straightforward manner. Casadi uses a heuristic to decide which is cheaper. A high value of 'jac_penalty' makes it less likely for the heurstic to chose the full Jacobian strategy. The special value -1 indicates never to use the full Jacobian strategycasadi::FunctionInternal
jacobian_optionsOT_DICTOptions to be passed to a Jacobian constructorcasadi::FunctionInternal

jit_optionsOT_DICTOptions to be passed to the jit compiler.casadi::FunctionInternal
jit_serializeOT_STRINGSpecify behaviour when serializing a jitted function: SOURCE|link|embed.casadi::FunctionInternal
jit_temp_suffixOT_BOOLUse a temporary (seemingly random) filename suffix for generated code and libraries. This is desired for thread-safety. This behaviour may defeat caching compiler wrappers. Default: truecasadi::FunctionInternal

2856  for (size_t iind = 0; iind < n_in_; ++iind) {
2857  // Add contribution
2858  MX a = mtimes(*J_it++, all_fseed[iind]);
2859  all_fsens[oind] = all_fsens[oind].is_empty(true) ? a : all_fsens[oind] + a;
2860  }
2861  }

2865  v = horzsplit(all_fsens[i]);
2866  casadi_assert_dev(v.size() == nfwd);
2867  for (size_t d = 0; d < nfwd; ++d) fsens[d][i] = reshape(v[d], size_out(i));
2868  }
2869  } else {
2870  // Evaluate in batches
2871  casadi_assert_dev(enable_forward_ || enable_fd_);
2872  casadi_int max_nfwd = max_num_dir_;

2874  while (!has_forward(max_nfwd)) max_nfwd/=2;
2875  }
2876  casadi_int offset = 0;
2877  while (offset<nfwd) {
2878  // Number of derivatives, in this batch
2879  casadi_int nfwd_batch = std::min(nfwd-offset, max_nfwd);
2880

2882  std::vector<MX> darg;
2883  darg.reserve(n_in_ + n_out_ + n_in_);

2885  darg.insert(darg.end(), res.begin(), res.end());

2887  for (casadi_int i=0; i<n_in_; ++i) {
2888  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) v[d] = fseed[offset+d][i];
2889  darg.push_back(horzcat(v));
2890  }
2891

2893  Function dfcn = self().forward(nfwd_batch);
2894  std::vector<MX> x = dfcn(darg);
2895 
2896  casadi_assert_dev(x.size()==n_out_);
2897

2899  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) fsens[offset+d].resize(n_out_);
2900  for (casadi_int i=0; i<n_out_; ++i) {
2901  if (size2_out(i)>0) {
2902  v = horzsplit(x[i], size2_out(i));
2903  casadi_assert_dev(v.size()==nfwd_batch);
2904  } else {
2905  v = std::vector<MX>(nfwd_batch, MX(size_out(i)));
2906  }
2907  for (casadi_int d=0; d<nfwd_batch; ++d) fsens[offset+d][i] = v[d];
2908  }
2909 
2910  // Update offset
2911  offset += nfwd_batch;
2912  }
2913  }
2914  }

766  d_nlp->lam[i] = d_bounds.lam_xl[i]+d_bounds.lam_xu[i];
767  }
768  }
769 
770  // Set multipliers to nan
771  casadi_fill(d_nlp->lam_p, np_, nan);
772 
773  // Reset f, g
774  d_nlp->objective = nan;
775  casadi_fill(d_nlp->z + nx_, ng_, nan);
776 
777  // Check the provided inputs
778  check_inputs(m);
779 
780  // Solve the NLP
781  int flag = solve(m);
782 
783  // Join statistics (introduced for parallel oracle facilities)
784  join_results(m);
785 
786  // Calculate multiplers
787  if ((calc_f_ || calc_g_ || calc_lam_x_ || calc_lam_p_) && !flag) {
788  const double lam_f = 1.;
789  m->arg[0] = d_nlp->z;
790  m->arg[1] = d_nlp->p;
791  m->arg[2] = &lam_f;
792  m->arg[3] = d_nlp->lam + nx_;
793  m->res[0] = calc_f_ ? &d_nlp->objective : nullptr;
794  m->res[1] = calc_g_ ? d_nlp->z + nx_ : nullptr;
795  m->res[2] = calc_lam_x_ ? d_nlp->lam : nullptr;
796  m->res[3] = calc_lam_p_ ? d_nlp->lam_p : nullptr;
797  if (calc_function(m, "nlp_grad")) {
798  casadi_warning("Failed to calculate multipliers");
799  }
800  if (calc_lam_x_) casadi_scal(nx_, -1., d_nlp->lam);
801  if (calc_lam_p_) casadi_scal(np_, -1., d_nlp->lam_p);
802  }
803 
804  // Make sure that an optimal solution is consistant with bounds
805  if (bound_consistency_ && !flag) {
806  bound_consistency(nx_+ng_, d_nlp->z, d_nlp->lam, d_nlp->lbz, d_nlp->ubz);
807  }
808 
809  // Get optimal solution
810  casadi_copy(d_nlp->z, nx_, d_nlp->x);
811 
812 
813 
814  if (p_nlp->detect_bounds.ng==0) {
815  casadi_copy(d_nlp->z + nx_, ng_, d_nlp->g);
816  casadi_copy(d_nlp->lam, nx_, d_nlp->lam_x);
817  casadi_copy(d_nlp->lam + nx_, ng_, d_nlp->lam_g);
818  } else {
819 
820  auto& d_bounds = d_nlp->detect_bounds;
821  const auto& p_bounds = p_nlp->detect_bounds;
822 
823  casadi_fill(d_nlp->lam_x, nx_, 0.);
824  casadi_fill(d_nlp->lam_g, p_bounds.ng, 0.);
825 
826  casadi_int k = 0;
827  casadi_int k_normal = 0;
828  for (casadi_int i=0;i<p_bounds.ng;++i) {
829  if (p_bounds.is_simple[i]) {
830  casadi_int j = p_bounds.target_x[k];
831  if (d_nlp->g) d_nlp->g[i] = d_bounds.a[k]*d_nlp->z[j]+d_bounds.b[k];
832  k++;
833  } else {
834  if (d_nlp->g) d_nlp->g[i] = d_nlp->z[nx_+k_normal];
835  if (d_nlp->lam_g) d_nlp->lam_g[i] = d_nlp->lam[nx_+k_normal];
836  k_normal++;
837  }
838  }
839 
840  for (casadi_int i=0;i<nx_;++i) {
841  if (d_bounds.target_l[i]<nx_) {
842  if (d_nlp->lam_x) d_nlp->lam_x[i] += (d_nlp->lam[i]<0)*d_nlp->lam[i];
843  } else {
844  if (d_nlp->lam_g)
845  d_nlp->lam_g[d_bounds.target_l[i]-nx_] += (d_nlp->lam[i]<0)*d_nlp->lam[i];
846  }
847  if (d_bounds.target_u[i]<nx_) {
848  if (d_nlp->lam_x) d_nlp->lam_x[i] += (d_nlp->lam[i]>0)*d_nlp->lam[i];
849  } else {
850  if (d_nlp->lam_g)
851  d_nlp->lam_g[d_bounds.target_u[i]-nx_] += (d_nlp->lam[i]>0)*d_nlp->lam[i];
852  }
853  }
854  }
855 
856 
857 
858  casadi_copy(d_nlp->lam_p, np_, d_nlp->lam_p);
859  casadi_copy(&d_nlp->objective, 1, d_nlp->f);
860 
861  if (error_on_fail_ && !m->success)
862  casadi_error("nlpsol process failed. "
863  "Set 'error_on_fail' option to false to ignore this error.");
864  return flag;
865  }

2012  for (i=0; i<n_in_; ++i) inames.push_back("fwd_" + name_in_[i]);
2013  // Names of outputs
2014  std::vector<std::string> onames;
2015  for (i=0; i<n_out_; ++i) onames.push_back("fwd_" + name_out_[i]);
2016  // Options
2017  Dict opts = combine(forward_options_, der_options_);
2018  opts = combine(opts, generate_options("forward"));
2019  if (!enable_forward_) opts = fd_options_;
2020  opts["derivative_of"] = self();
2021  // Generate derivative function
2022  casadi_assert_dev(enable_forward_ || enable_fd_);
2023  if (enable_forward_) {
2024  f = get_forward(nfwd, fname, inames, onames, opts);
2025  } else {
2026  // Get FD method
2027  if (fd_method_.empty() || fd_method_=="central") {
2028  f = Function::create(new CentralDiff(fname, nfwd), opts);
2029  } else if (fd_method_=="forward") {
2030  f = Function::create(new ForwardDiff(fname, nfwd), opts);
2031  } else if (fd_method_=="backward") {
2032  f = Function::create(new BackwardDiff(fname, nfwd), opts);
2033  } else if (fd_method_=="smoothing") {
2034  f = Function::create(new Smoothing(fname, nfwd), opts);
2035  } else {
2036  casadi_error("Unknown 'fd_method': " + fd_method_);
2037  }
2038  }
2039  // Consistency check for inputs
2040  casadi_assert_dev(f.n_in()==n_in_ + n_out_ + n_in_);
2041  casadi_int ind=0;
2042  for (i=0; i<n_in_; ++i) f.assert_size_in(ind++, size1_in(i), size2_in(i));
2043  for (i=0; i<n_out_; ++i) f.assert_size_in(ind++, size1_out(i), size2_out(i));
2044  for (i=0; i<n_in_; ++i) f.assert_size_in(ind++, size1_in(i), nfwd*size2_in(i));
2045  // Consistency check for outputs
2046  casadi_assert_dev(f.n_out()==n_out_);
2047  for (i=0; i<n_out_; ++i) f.assert_size_out(i, size1_out(i), nfwd*size2_out(i));
2048  // Save to cache
2049  tocache(f);
2050  }
2051  return f;
2052  }

993  MX fwd_ubx = fseed[NLPSOL_UBX] = MX::sym("fwd_ubx", repmat(x.sparsity(), 1, nfwd));
994  MX fwd_lbg = fseed[NLPSOL_LBG] = MX::sym("fwd_lbg", repmat(g.sparsity(), 1, nfwd));
995  MX fwd_ubg = fseed[NLPSOL_UBG] = MX::sym("fwd_ubg", repmat(g.sparsity(), 1, nfwd));
996  MX fwd_p = fseed[NLPSOL_P] = MX::sym("fwd_p", repmat(p.sparsity(), 1, nfwd));
997 
998  // Guesses are unused
999  for (NlpsolInput i : {NLPSOL_X0, NLPSOL_LAM_X0, NLPSOL_LAM_G0}) {
1000  fseed[i] = MX(repmat(Sparsity(arg[i].size()), 1, nfwd));
1001  }
1002 
1003  // nlp_grad has the signature
1004  // (x, p, lam_f, lam_g) -> (f, g, grad_x, grad_p)
1005  // with lam_f=1 and lam_g=lam_g, grad_x = -lam_x, grad_p=-lam_p
1006  Function nlp_grad = get_function("nlp_grad");
1007 
1008  // fwd_nlp_grad has the signature
1009  // (x, p, lam_f, lam_g, f, g, grad_x, grad_p,
1010  // fwd_x, fwd_p, fwd_lam_f, fwd_lam_g)
1011  // -> (fwd_f, fwd_g, fwd_grad_x, fwd_grad_p)
1012  Function fwd_nlp_grad = nlp_grad.forward(nfwd);
1013 
1014  // Calculate sensitivities from fwd_p
1015  std::vector<MX> vv = {x, p, 1, lam_g, f, g, -lam_x, -lam_p, 0., fwd_p, 0., 0.};
1016  vv = fwd_nlp_grad(vv);
1017  MX fwd_g_p = vv.at(1);
1018  MX fwd_gL_p = vv.at(2);
1019 
1020  // Propagate forward seeds
1021  MX fwd_alpha_x = (if_else(lbIx, fwd_lbx, 0) + if_else(ubIx, fwd_ubx, 0))
1022  - if_else(iIx, fwd_gL_p, 0);
1023  MX fwd_alpha_g = (if_else(ubIg, fwd_ubg, 0) + if_else(lbIg, fwd_lbg, 0))
1024  - if_else(bIg, fwd_g_p, 0);
1025  MX v = MX::vertcat({fwd_alpha_x, fwd_alpha_g});
1026 
1027  // Solve
1028  v = MX::solve(H, v, sens_linsol_, sens_linsol_options_);
1029 
1030  // Extract sensitivities in x, lam_x and lam_g
1031  std::vector<MX> v_split = vertsplit(v, {0, nx_, nx_+ng_});
1032  MX fwd_x = v_split.at(0);
1033  MX fwd_lam_g = v_split.at(1);
1034 
1035  // Calculate sensitivities in lam_x, lam_g
1036  vv = {x, p, 1, lam_g, f, g, -lam_x, -lam_p,
1037  fwd_x, fwd_p, 0, fwd_lam_g};
1038  vv = fwd_nlp_grad(vv);
1039  MX fwd_f = vv.at(0);
1040  MX fwd_g = vv.at(1);
1041  MX fwd_lam_x = -vv.at(2);
1042  MX fwd_lam_p = -vv.at(3);
1043 
1044  // Forward sensitivities
1045  std::vector<MX> fsens(NLPSOL_NUM_OUT);
1046  fsens[NLPSOL_X] = fwd_x;
1047  fsens[NLPSOL_F] = fwd_f;
1048  fsens[NLPSOL_G] = fwd_g;
1049  fsens[NLPSOL_LAM_X] = fwd_lam_x;
1050  fsens[NLPSOL_LAM_G] = fwd_lam_g;
1051  fsens[NLPSOL_LAM_P] = fwd_lam_p;
1052 
1053  // Gather return values
1054  arg.insert(arg.end(), res.begin(), res.end());
1055  arg.insert(arg.end(), fseed.begin(), fseed.end());
1056  res = fsens;
1057 
1058  Dict options = opts;
1059  options["allow_duplicate_io_names"] = true;
1060 
1061  return Function(name, arg, res, inames, onames, options);
1062  }

1537  double fwd_cost = static_cast<double>(use_fwd ? granularity_row : granularity_col) *
1538  sp_w*static_cast<double>(D1.size2());

1540  (1-sp_w)*static_cast<double>(D2.size2());

1544  "(fwd cost: " + str(fwd_cost) + ", adj cost: " + str(adj_cost) + ")");

1564  std::swap(granularity_col, granularity_row);
1565  std::swap(r, rT);
1566  }

1570  casadi_int diff = coarse_col[k+1]-coarse_col[k];
1571  casadi_int new_diff = diff/subdivision;
1572  if (diff%subdivision>0) new_diff++;
1573  std::vector<casadi_int> temp = range(coarse_col[k], coarse_col[k+1], new_diff);
1574  fine_col.insert(fine_col.end(), temp.begin(), temp.end());
1575  }

1579  casadi_int new_diff = diff/subdivision;
1580  if (diff%subdivision>0) new_diff++;
1581  std::vector<casadi_int> temp = range(coarse_row[k], coarse_row[k+1], new_diff);
1582  fine_row.insert(fine_row.end(), temp.begin(), temp.end());
1583  }
